Package pds.cdf

Class Summary
ADRecord Attribute Descriptor Record (ADR).
AEDRecord Attribute Entry Descriptor Record (AEDR) An Attribute Entry Descriptor Record (AEDR) contains a description of an attribute entry.
Attribute Generic attribute information.
CDF Parse a CDF file and create lists of records, attributes and variables defined in the file.
CDRecord CDF Descriptor Record (CDR).
Check Determine if the CDF file is compliant with archive requirements.
Constant  
Dump Parses a CDF file and displays detailed information about the internal structure and contents of the file.
GDRecord Global Descriptor Record (CDR).
Record The stub record all CDF records are based on.
UIRecord Variable Value Record (VVR) Variable Value Records (VVRs) are used to store one or more variable records in a single-file CDF.
Variable Variable information.
VDRecord Variable Descriptor Record (VDR).
VVRecord Variable Value Record (VVR) Variable Value Records (VVRs) are used to store one or more variable records in a single-file CDF.
VXRecord Variable Index Record (VXR) (VXRs) are used in single-file CDFs to store the file offsets of any lower level of VXRs or Variable Values Records (VVRs).
